{"audit":{"b_max":400,"directrix_base_rate":0.0337375,"directrix_support":5398,"distinct_kernel_count_for_e_window":258,"e_max":400,"first_kernel_mismatches":[],"first_reduction_mismatches":[],"kernel_mismatch_count":0,"pair_count":160000,"reduction_mismatch_count":0},"canonical_hash":"cb9a820a9fede0ead32370d76f3fa36d2005a11301f9d0c2d4c1810934bddab5","cert_readiness":"Ready for a small structural theorem cert if desired; otherwise this should be merged into the algebraic-status ledger as PROVEN_STRUCTURAL_DIVISIBILITY_REDUCTION.","parameters":{"b_max":400,"e_max":400,"sample_limit":25},"proof":["The directrix target tests whether d*d*d/e is an integer, i.e. whether e divides d*d*d.","Since d=b+e, d is congruent to b modulo e.","Congruence is compatible with multiplication, so d*d*d is congruent to b*b*b modulo e.","Therefore e divides d*d*d iff e divides b*b*b.","For e=product p^r, the condition e|b*b*b is equivalent prime-by-prime to r <= 3*v_p(b).","Thus v_p(b) >= ceil(r/3) for every prime p|e, which is exactly kernel3(e)|b."],"relation_to_stage21":"Stage 21 already ran the b_only/e_only controls. e_only lift was 2.43, b_only lift was 2.61, qa_orbit_family9 and qa_orbit_id9 lifted 3.93, drop_raw_be lifted 6.57, and derived_products lifted 7.17. This closure explains the target as generator divisibility e|b*b*b; orbit features can remain predictive, but the target is not an unexplained conic invariant.","sample_positive_rows":[{"b":1,"d":2,"directrix_integer":true,"e":1,"kernel3_e":1,"minimal_b_condition":"b divisible by 1"},{"b":2,"d":3,"directrix_integer":true,"e":1,"kernel3_e":1,"minimal_b_condition":"b divisible by 1"},{"b":3,"d":4,"directrix_integer":true,"e":1,"kernel3_e":1,"minimal_b_condition":"b divisible by 1"},{"b":4,"d":5,"directrix_integer":true,"e":1,"kernel3_e":1,"minimal_b_condition":"b divisible by 1"},{"b":5,"d":6,"directrix_integer":true,"e":1,"kernel3_e":1,"minimal_b_condition":"b divisible by 1"},{"b":6,"d":7,"directrix_integer":true,"e":1,"ker